data.body:
Would be nice for the con yard's progress bars to always have a fixed position.
I like to know if my teammate has a defense building ready without having to type first.

But right now, whatever is build first, is drawn first. So if my mate only builds defenses, but no buildings, the defense progress bar is shown where the buildings progress bar normally is.

It would be better if the locations is always the same, so you always know whats going on.

Also, colors are too similar.
Something like cyan for the building progress bar and pink for the defese building bar would be better, so you can tell the difference by one look.

BTW, the progress bars are drawn after selection boxes, it should be the other way around.

So instead:
wr.DrawSelectionBox(self, Color.White);
DrawHealthBar(wr, xy, Xy);
DrawExtraBars(wr, xy, Xy);
DrawUnitPath(wr);

Better:
DrawHealthBar(wr, xy, Xy);
DrawExtraBars(wr, xy, Xy);
DrawUnitPath(wr);
wr.DrawSelectionBox(self, Color.White);

